Data from database: Health Nutrition and Population Statistics

Country Name: Adults (ages 15+) and children (0-14 years) living with HIV
Country Code: Adults and children living with HIV refers to the number of people ages 0-49 (adult ages 15-49 and children ages 0-14) who are infected with HIV.

Country Name: Condom use, population ages 15-24, female (% of females ages 15-24)
Country Code: Condom use, female is the percentage of the female population ages 15-24 who used a condom at last intercourse in the last 12 months.
2015 [YR2015]: Demographic and Health Surveys, and UNAIDS.
